=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LFNoise2_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark mixed sound, with complex oscillator character around 55 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 55.4785
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.0759
  harmonic_regularity: 0.1179
  pitch_clarity: 25.6384
  inharmonicity: 0.0682
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -34.4544
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LFNoise2 Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LFNoise2.html
// Tags: LFNoise2, Classes, noise, modulation
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ LFNoise2.ar(1000, 0.25) }.play;

// modulate frequency

{ LFNoise2.ar(XLine.kr(1000, 10000, 10), 0.25) }.play;

// as frequency modulator
(
{ SinOsc.ar(
        LFNoise2.ar(4, 400, 450),
        0, 0.2
    )
}.play;
)

// freq is the rate of interpolation points
{ var freq = 1000; [LFNoise2.ar(freq), Impulse.ar(freq)] }.plot
